# ShipFee — Frontend & Deploy Rules

## Source of truth

- Edit **`customer-app/`**, **`shipper-app/`**, **`admin-app/`** at repo root.
- **`public/`** is Vercel build output. It is overwritten by `npm run build`.
- After any frontend edit, run **`npm run build`** before commit so `public/` stays in sync.
- Commit both the root app folder and the matching `public/` copy.

## Deploy to production

- Pushing a feature branch / opening a PR does **not** deploy production.
- Production (Vercel + Render) updates only when changes land on **`master`** (merge PR or push).
- Backend: edit `server/` only (Render root directory = `server`).
- Frontend Vercel: Build Command `npm run build`, Output Directory `public`.

## Customer app performance reminders

- List API uses `page`/`limit`; do not load the full catalog on home.
- Prefer Supabase menu hydrate over Puppeteer scrape on detail.
- Do not persist fabricated template menus to `server/menus/`.

See `AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, and `DEPLOYMENT_GUIDE.md` for full detail.
